00:01:44.800 --> 00:01:54.600
 Leading to a 1-0 break, I told the players that we had to play very mature in the second half. 

00:01:55.600 --> 00:01:59.640
 I even compared it to the style of the Italian team. 

00:01:59.640 --> 00:02:02.880
 To how the Italians would play if they were leading 1: 0. 

00:02:02.880 --> 00:02:10.760
 You have to compact the playing field, allow your opponent to stay on the ball and try to score a goal ... 

00:02:10.760 --> 00:02:14.560
 ... or be careful and use the rival's error. 

00:02:14.560 --> 00:02:17.120
 That's what happened. 

00:02:17.120 --> 00:02:23.840
